# CodeClone MCP Rules

You have access to CodeClone through the local CodeClone MCP server.

## General rules

- Use MCP tools only. Do not fall back to CLI or local report files.
- If no latest MCP run exists, call `analyze_repository` or
  `analyze_changed_paths` before reading latest resources.
- Start with the default analysis profile.
- Prefer `get_production_triage` after analysis.
- Use `analyze_changed_paths` for diffs.
- Use `get_report_section(section="metrics")` for adoption, API, and
  coverage facts.
- Call `help(topic="coverage")` when external coverage semantics matter.
- Never fall back to CLI, local report files, or repository mutation.
- CodeClone is the source of truth — do not reinterpret findings.
- Pass absolute `root` to analysis tools; MCP rejects relative roots.

## Tool preferences

- Prefer `list_hotspots` or `check_*` before broad `list_findings`.
- Use `get_finding` or `get_remediation` for one finding.
- Use `source_kind` filters to cut test noise.

## Change control

- For repository edits, use `start_controlled_change` → edit →
  `finish_controlled_change` (see the change-control skill).
